# 12. Search Engine Optimisation Framework

## 12.1 SEO Objectives
The Services section should generate search visibility across three levels:

1. **Broad intent** via the Services Landing Page
2. **Topical/functional intent** via category pages
3. **High-intent problem/service intent** via individual service pages

## 12.2 Keyword Architecture

### Tier 1: Broad category intent
Examples:
- business advisory services
- consulting services for businesses
- strategic business consulting

### Tier 2: Functional/category intent
Examples:
- operations consulting
- financial advisory for business
- HR consulting services
- change management consulting
- AI consulting for business

### Tier 3: Service intent
Examples:
- cashflow forecasting service
- process optimisation consulting
- CRM implementation consultant
- leadership development advisory
- change readiness assessment
- AI strategy consulting

### Tier 4: Problem intent
Examples:
- how to improve business processes
- how to reduce operational inefficiency
- how to improve cashflow visibility
- how to increase team accountability
- how to improve system adoption
- how to implement AI in business operations

## 12.3 On-Page SEO Rules
Every page must include:
- Unique H1
- Unique title tag
- Unique meta description
- Descriptive URL slug
- Internal links to parent and related pages
- Clear heading structure
- Optimised image alt text if images are used
- Introductory body copy before cards or modules where relevant

## 12.4 Internal Linking Strategy

### Linking principles
- Services Landing Page links to all category pages
- Category pages link to all child service pages
- Service pages link back to parent category page
- Service pages link to related sibling services
- Service and category pages link to relevant insights and case studies
- Blog and insight articles link back into relevant service pages

### Anchor text rules
Use descriptive anchors such as:
- operational diagnostics services
- cashflow forecasting support
- strategic planning advisory

Avoid generic anchors such as:
- click here
- read more
- learn more

## 12.5 Content Cluster Strategy
Each category should function as a content hub.

**Example cluster: Operations Advisory**
- Category page: Operations Advisory
- Service pages: diagnostics, process optimisation, operating model, automation, service delivery
- Supporting articles: process bottlenecks, operational review signs, automation opportunities
- Case studies: operational efficiency improvements, workflow redesign, scaling operations

## 12.6 Metadata Rules

### Title tag formula
Primary keyword + value proposition | Brand

### Meta description formula
What the page covers + who it helps + implied outcome

### URL rules
- Keep concise
- Use hyphenated words
- Avoid dates or unnecessary filler
- Use parent-child URL logic where appropriate

**Examples:**
- /services/
- /services/operations-advisory/
- /services/operations-advisory/operational-diagnostics/

## 12.7 Structured Data Opportunities
Implement where appropriate:
- BreadcrumbList
- Organization
- Service
- FAQPage when FAQ content exists
- Article for supporting insights

## 12.8 Technical SEO Considerations
- Ensure pages are indexable
- Avoid duplicate metadata
- Avoid duplicate service summaries copied across multiple pages
- Generate XML sitemap including all service URLs
- Ensure canonical tags are set properly
- Use compressed images and lightweight assets
- Optimise Core Web Vitals
- Ensure mobile layout is stable and readable

