# 16. Governance Rules for Ongoing Expansion

## 16.1 When adding a new service
Check:
- Does it fit within an existing category?
- Is it distinct enough to warrant its own page?
- Does it overlap with an existing service?
- What keyword opportunity does it target?
- What related pages need to link to it?

## 16.2 Avoiding duplication
- Do not create pages that differ only by wording
- Consolidate overlapping services where intent is too similar
- Use category pages to capture broad themes and service pages to capture specific intent

## 16.3 Maintaining consistency
Every new page must follow:
- approved layout structure
- tone rules
- CTA rules
- metadata standards
- internal linking standards

